# ✒ Metadata
#     - Title: Git Ignore Rules (Message Vault Edition - v2.0)
#     - File Name: .gitignore
#     - Relative Path: .gitignore
#     - Artifact Type: config
#     - Version: 2.0.0
#     - Date: 2026-07-20
#     - Update: Monday, July 20, 2026
#     - Author: Dennis 'dendogg' Smaltz
#     - A.I. Acknowledgement: Anthropic - Claude Opus 4.8
#     - Signature: ︻デ═─── ✦ ✦ ✦ | Aim Twice, Shoot Once!
#
# ✒ Changelog:
#     - 2.0.0 (2026-07-20) [Anthropic - Claude Opus 4.8] — Release privacy sweep. Added the
#       personal-data classes this app can actually produce: exported archives (.jsonl,
#       .db, .zip, .mvault), extracted attachments, and the app/debug/ capture tree
#       (screen recordings, screenshots, bug reports, traces) taken against the owner's
#       real message corpus. Added device-pull, profiling, and credential-bearing paths.
#       Media ignores are global with explicit allowances for shipped app resources and
#       branding source art so the build is never starved of its own assets.
#     - 1.0.0 (2026-07-20) [Anthropic - Claude Opus 4.8] — Initial: standard Android/Gradle
#       ignores plus the machine-specific and stale-backup paths this repo actually carries.
#
# ✒ Description:
#     Keeps three categories out of version control: (1) anything regenerated by a build,
#     (2) anything specific to one machine or IDE, and (3) anything derived from the
#     owner's real SMS/MMS corpus. Message Vault reads private message data by design, so
#     any artifact it emits — an archive, an attachment, a screen recording of the UI
#     showing real conversations — is personal data and is irreversible once published.
#     Category three is treated as the strictest.
#
# ✒ Key Features:
#     - Personal data: exported archives, attachments, and the whole app/debug/ capture
#       tree are excluded by directory AND by extension, so a stray file dropped into a
#       new folder is still caught.
#     - Media is denied globally, then explicitly re-allowed for app/src/main/res/ and
#       branding/, which are the only image assets that legitimately belong to the repo.
#     - Build output: build/, app/build/, .gradle/, .kotlin/, *.apk, *.aab.
#     - Machine-specific: local.properties (absolute SDK path) and IDE state.
#     - Secrets: keystores and signing property files never enter history.
#     - Stale duplicates: .bak_headers/ is a copy of live docs and src; tracking it would
#       give a first-time reader two competing versions of the same files.
#
# ✒ Other Important Information:
#     - Dependencies: git.
#     - Compatible platforms: any git client.
#     - Ignoring a path does NOT untrack a file that is already committed, and does not
#       remove it from history. Anything previously committed must be dealt with
#       separately (git rm --cached, plus a history rewrite if it was ever pushed).
# ---------

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PERSONAL DATA — the owner's real messages. Never commit.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Debug capture tree: screen recordings and screenshots of the live app, which
# necessarily show real conversations, contact names, and phone numbers.
app/debug/
debug-captures/
screenshots/
screen-recordings/
recordings/
bug-reports/
traces/

# Exported archives produced by ArchiveEngine and the exporters.
exports/
export/
archives/
*.mvault
*.jsonl
*.ndjson
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# Extracted MMS attachments and anything pulled off the device.
attachments/
device-pull/
pulled/
sdcard/

# Archive containers.
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.7z
*.rar

# Loose tabular and contact dumps.
*.csv
*.tsv
*.vcf

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MEDIA — denied globally, since any image or video in this repo
# is presumed to be a capture of real message content until the
# allowances below say otherwise.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.bmp
*.webp
*.heic
*.heif
*.mp4
*.mov
*.mkv
*.webm
*.avi
*.m4v
*.3gp
*.mp3
*.m4a
*.aac
*.ogg
*.wav
*.amr

# Allowances: shipped app resources and branding source art. These are the only
# image assets that legitimately belong in the repository.
!app/src/main/res/**
!branding/**
!docs/assets/**

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECRETS AND CREDENTIALS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.jks
*.keystore
*.p12
*.pfx
*.pem
*.key
keystore.properties
signing.properties
secrets.properties
google-services.json
service-account*.json
.env
.env.*
*.credentials
*.token

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MACHINE-SPECIFIC — absolute SDK path, never portable
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
local.properties
.claude/settings.local.json

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BUILD OUTPUT
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
build/
app/build/
.gradle/
.kotlin/
.cxx/
out/
release/
*.apk
*.aab
*.ap_
*.dex
*.class
*.jar
!gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar
*.hprof
*.trace
captures/
lint-results*.html
lint-results*.xml
reports/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IDE AND EDITOR
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
.vscode/
*.swp
*~

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OS CRUFT
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STALE DUPLICATES AND BACKUPS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.bak_headers/
*.bak
*.orig
*.rej
*.tmp
*.log
